[bkg=bg.pbm][h1]AI survey among Amiga graphicians
by 11 graphicians


Eleven (11) graphcians were asked between Mid April to Mid May 2024 with focus on AI in art, and I got answer from all. There are other talent graphicians out there than these asked. The common thing among them, are that non of them is newbie in creating art in the scene. My aim was to select a mixture of graphicians (geographically, various groups, and in style). It might be a hint where the wind blows in replies. It may also be seen as a statement right now.

PARTICIPANTS
Archmage/Andromeda, Cheetah/Ephidrena, dan dee/Scarab, Facet/Lemon., farfar/FLEX^Loonies, Frost/Tulou, malmix/Nature, Prowler/Nectrarine, Razorback, Slayer/Ghostown and xeNusion/RNO

SURVEY QUESTIONS
1: Do you use/plan to use AI in your graphics or products?
2: Do you think AI-images should have own compo separated from "handcrafted" art in compos?
3: Are you worried that AI art will be fully accepted  in the scene?

Lets see their answers in order I got answers back (short form of questions used below for readiness). 

................................

Farfar:
-------

1: use/plan to use AI in your work?
I will use AI in assisting functions (to replace manual labour, like eg. Background removal or rotoscoping). I’ll also use AI for inspiration

2: AI-images separate compo?
I don’t think there is anything interesting in an AI generated compo, really. I don’t know why, but it just leaves me cold and uninterested. 

3: Worried AI art scene acceptance?
I’m not overly worried no.  

The thing about AI that I am most critical about, is that some people leave their own judgement and decisionmaking at the door. I think it does tend to make people stop reflecting for themselves, and just accept the AI’s output

Although maybe I do know why it leaves me cold.. like, when Made or Facet or Critikill create a piece of pixel art, they are setting a bar to strive for and learn from. With AI generated stuff, that just isnt the case. I feel inspired by talented craftsmen

Hm.. although.. thats also not entirely true. I do remember examples of ai pics that I found inspiring… but not often. I guess thr same could be said for lots of other inspiration sources :)

................................

Facet:
------

1: use/plan to use AI in your work?
We all know, AI is here to stay. I see AI as an extra point of inspiration and exploration. Sometimes it helps to visualise ideas of course. It's great!! Using AI as pixel tool is ridiculous. I started pixeling because I like to place pixel. Outsourcing that to AI is of course something I never will do. And what do I then have to do with all the spare time? pff.... ;D

2: AI-images separate compo?
No different compo. Why? then we should have had many other comps like the 'copy' + 'no-copy' compo.. or the 'with dPaint' vs 'with Photoshop'.. 

3: Worried AI art scene acceptance?
I'm not woried at all. As long we stay critical and positive. I am more woried about the ones blaming and shaming others. Let them use that energy to build or create something for our great scene instead of jepardising it.

................................

Razorback:
----------

1: use/plan to use AI in your work?
No

2: AI-images separate compo?
No

3: Worried AI art scene acceptance?
No

Only time AI should be accepted is in some coding category where the coder self built the AI and trained it with own produced data. Else its damn more lame than a dmeo built with UnrealEngine.. Someone else has done most of the work already :)

